COPS have arrested two prison warders accused of helping 16 prisoners escape from Sun City Prison in Joburg. Provincial Detectives dealing with the case managed to obtain information regarding the prison officials who allegedly helped the suspects escape. SEE:Â 16 PRISONERS ESCAPE FROM SUN CITY PRISON! The two prison officers were arrested on Thursday. Statements were obtained from both officers and a case docket has been opened. The two officers have denied the allegations against them. They remain in custody at the Mondeor Police Station. This is still a developing story, more info to follow.